The paper proposes a new architecture for deep reinforcement learning in partially observable environments. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed architecture involves the use of convolutional neural networks (cs.CV) and recurrent neural networks (cs.RO) to handle time series data. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Q-learning (cs.AI) and deep neural networks (cs.NE) in the proposed architecture. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.CV, cs.RO, and cs.NE.
